      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It can be crushing to know that your kids, who should be supporting and caring for you, are shouldering the weight of your care. It's natural to feel like a burden, especially when you've lived a full life and expected to be able to continue on your own terms. Have you considered their sacrifices as equal to the sacrifices you've made for them, and perhaps it's time to redefine what it means to be \"burdensome\" or \"supportive\"?",
